    <p>Mr. RAFFERTY: (Singing) You know I need your love. You got that hold over me. As long as I got your love, you know that I'll never leave. When I wanted you to share my life, I had no doubt in my mind. And it's been you, woman, right down the line. </p>
    <p>BLOCK: And if those two songs don't stir up old memories for you, this one just might do it. </p>
    <p>(Soundbite of song, "Stuck in the Middle With You") </p>
    <p>Mr. RAFFERTY: (Singing) Well, I don't know why I came here tonight. I got a feeling that something ain't right. </p>
    <p>BLOCK: That's Rafferty's 1972 hit with his band Stealers Wheel, "Stuck in the Middle With You." Twenty years later, Quentin Tarantino used the track in his film "Reservoir Dogs." </p>
