    <p>NORRIS: Singer-songwriter Gerry Rafferty. He died today. He was 63 years old. </p>
    <p>(Soundbite of song, "Stuck in the Middle With You") </p>
    <p>Mr. RAFFERTY: (Singing) It's so hard to keep this smile from my face. Losing control, yeah, I'm all over the place. Clowns to the left of me, jokers to the right, here I am, stuck in the middle with you. </p>
<h1> "Immigration Enforcement Working, Numbers Show" </h1>
    <p>MICHELE NORRIS, host: </p>
    <p>From NPR News, this is ALL THINGS CONSIDERED. I'm Michele Norris. </p>
    <p>MELISSA BLOCK, host: </p>
