    <p>Mr. MICHAEL FLOOD (President, Los Angeles Regional Food Bank): There are so many new people in line. I can't tell you how many times I've heard from somebody, saying: I used to be a donor, and I never thought I was going to be standing in line at a food pantry, needing help and needing assistance. </p>
