    <p>HORSLEY: In that 2006 speech, Sperling described himself as a pro-growth progressive, which means he's concerned with both the size of the economic pie and the way it's divided up.</p>
    <p>BLOCK: The notion that a rising tide should lift all boats is the core aspiration for what economic policy should be in our country.</p>
